introduction.en-US: A powerful AI platform that bridges the gap between educators and students, enabling objective, real-time assessments of writing development.

metadataDescription.en-US: As Design Lead, I guided a multidisciplinary team to integrate branding, human factors, and functionality, creating a solution that bridges physical tools and digital insights.

paragraph1.en-US: With Rune, we empower educators and support students by transforming writing assessment from subjective observation to precise, data-driven insight. All while enhancing class engagement and the learning environment.

paragraph2.en-US: Our pen design and intuitive UI offer an integrated approach that enhances understanding, fosters student confidence, and promotes academic success.

paragraph1.en-US: Rune integrates a smart pen with an intuitive user interface to provide real-time insights into student writing. By combining advanced data tracking with a user-friendly design, Rune allows educators to identify and address student challenges with precision. This solution fosters student confidence, streamlines assessment, and promotes academic success through actionable feedback and engagement tools.

introduction.en-US: A reimagined thermostat that blends luxury and innovative technology to deliver seamless integration into modern homes.

paragraph1.en-US: Our goal was to redefine the Nest thermostat as a standalone brand, combining high-end luxury with cutting-edge technology. We focused on designing a product that integrates effortlessly into modern homes, delivering exceptional control and efficiency in climate management.

We redesigned the Nest thermostat with a focus on user-centered design, utilizing A/B testing to refine the interface and ensure intuitive interactions. The new design emphasizes clarity and functionality, blending luxury with innovative technology. User research and testing informed key decisions, such as optimizing button selection and navigation flow.

metadataDescription.en-US: I helped lead the thermostat team, guiding design direction and overseeing user testing to refine the experience. Our focus was on creating a seamless blend of luxury, functionality, and innovation for modern homes.

excerpt.en-US: Here is a quick description of this project.

introduction.en-US: A project encompassing branding, marketing, and UX/UI design, showing how designing with each in mind can create lasting impact.

paragraph1.en-US: Our objective was to transform the Nest thermostat into a standalone brand that embodies both high-end luxury and innovative technology. We aimed to create a product that seamlessly integrates into modern homes while providing unparalleled control and efficiency in climate management.
Our design emphasizes innovation, aiming to reinvent the thermostat by enhancing its features to create a unique and luxurious experience without sacrificing practicality and usability.

text.en-US: At first our team researched ways to ease and relieve writing pain associated with dysgraphia and fine motor regression, but once we stepped back and examined all our insights, we realized a much bigger gap in the education system as it is today.

paragraph1.en-US: Traditional educational approaches rely heavily on teacher observation to identify issues. While dedicated, teachers face large class sizes and limited resources, making it difficult to catch nuanced writing issues.

text.en-US: Every classroom has students who face unseen challenges. One of the most overlooked yet impactful difficulties is related to writing development. Writing difficulties often go unnoticed or are misunderstood, affecting students confidence, academic performance, and engagement.

blurb.en-US: We heard numerous stories of people experiencing misunderstanding with their teachers. Expressing a student-teacher disconnect across all of our insights. This became a large problem area we felt the need to address.

quote2.en-US: “No accommodations are yet made for me, my teachers aren't even aware of anything named dysgraphia"

introduction.en-US: An annual design competition at SCAD that fosters innovation and collaboration across disciplines, inspiring students to push creative boundaries and develop impactful solutions.

paragraph1.en-US: Tasked with designing and using Webflow to develop the website for SCAD StartUp 2025. Each year FLUX hosts StartUp, a design competition that sparks creativity and innovation. We redefined the information architecture and created a modern, clean design.

A clean, modern design that emphasizes the theme of this years competition. After fledging out information architecture, we were able to put together something that is delightful and easily digestible.

metadataDescription.en-US: As Design Lead, I helped define the style and direction of the website. I also led the build in Webflow.

excerpt.en-US: UX/UI Design, Electronics, Programming, Product Design

introduction.en-US: A modern take on the classic CD player, Discus combines gesture-based controls with sleek design to transform the way users interact with their music.

paragraph1.en-US: Discus was born from a desire to redefine the interaction with physical media, focusing on CDs as both a nostalgic format and a design element. The goal was to create a product that felt intuitive and innovative while honoring the tactile experience of traditional music players.

Discus features a gesture-controlled interface that allows users to swipe left and right to change tracks and up and down to switch CDs. It automatically starts playback when approached, delivering a seamless and engaging experience. The layered acrylic design emphasizes simplicity and showcases the CDs as a central visual element.

metadataDescription.en-US: I conceptualized, engineered, and built Discus from the ground up. I designed the gesture control system, prototyped the physical structure, and integrated hardware and software to create a cohesive and intuitive experience.

introduction.en-US: A personalized skincare app that connects weather data to your routine, offering tailored guidance for healthier skin. Integrating real-time insights like UV levels and explaining their impact.

paragraph1.en-US: Lumo was created to bridge the gap between skincare and environmental factors, addressing the limitations of existing apps with poor UX and excessive monetization. By integrating weather data into personalized routines, Lumo provides meaningful insights that empower users to make informed decisions for healthier skin.

Lumo combines real-time weather updates, like UV levels, with tailored skincare routines and reminders. The app explains the impact of environmental factors on skin health, offering expert guidance and promoting healthier habits.

metadataDescription.en-US: I directed the design strategy, focusing on creating an intuitive and visually engaging interface. I also mentored two graphic designers on my team, teaching them Figma and guiding them in best practices for crafting effective user interfaces.

heading.en-US: This is about empowering both educators and learners.

text.en-US: AI-powered detection of writing irregularities and difficulties—integrated into a smart writing device—has the potential to transform how we approach writing development.
While testing different physical form factors, our team also dove into crafting the digital experience that would pair with our smart pen.

Equipped with multiple sensors, the pen tracks key handwriting metrics such as angle, grip, pressure, and speed. This data helps identify students who may be struggling with writing mechanics, offering a more objective and actionable way to assess and support student development.

title.en-US: How do we integrate this into classrooms?

text.en-US: Inspired by game-based learning platforms, Rune replaces digital input with a smart pen, allowing students to participate in activities and quizzes by writing on physical paper.
